It represents what happened as the two sides of a picture, the plebs looking for the fulfilment of the promises made to them on the one side, and on the other Appius doing his best to frustrate their hopes. The construction is used by Sallust, Jug. 98. 2, and frequently by Tacitus, not by Cicero or Caesar.
